ResourceHeader.ResourceName: GOES 15 Magnetospheric Proton Detector (MAGPD) data with average energy of 95 keV at 1 min Time Resolution in Spacecraft Coordinates
ResourceHeader.Description: The GOES 15 Magnetospheric Proton Detector (MAGPD) are essentially the same as the Energetic Particle Sensor (EPS) on GOES 8-12. For more information, please see Onsager et al. 1996, Operational uses of the GOES energetic particle detectors, in GOES 8 and Beyond, Proc. SPIE, Vol. 2812, edited by E. R. Washwell, pp. 281-290, Bellingham, WA. These data file contain mainly information on the proton count rates and fluxes from 95 to 475 keV. Data files contain long descriptive header.
ResourceHeader.Acknowledgement: NASA Office of Space Science Applications (United States), NOAA National Environmental Satellite Service (United States), Terry G. Onsager

InformationURL.Name: GOES N, O, and P Brochure
InformationURL.Description: Information about the magnetometers onboard GOES 15

AccessURL.Name: Direct access to the GOES 15 Magnetospheric Proton Detector (MAGPD) data
AccessURL.Description: Direct link to the GOES 15 Magnetospheric Proton Detector (MAGPD) data in CSV format as well as the energetic particle data from other GOES spacecraft. The data are sorted by year, month, spacecraft, and file type. The file names indicates the data type, spacecraft number, year, month, and resolution. For example, g15_magpd_19me15_1m_20110101_20110131.csv, indicates GOES 15 magnetometer data at 1 min time resolution from 2011-01-01 to 2011-01-31.

TimeSpan.Note: Time format in data files is year-month-day hour:minute:seconds. Data file may fill out the first month and last month with flags.
